Date: Fri, 21 May 2004
From: Steve Edwards <s.edwards@vla.defra.gsi.gov.uk>


Scientists wishing access to the VLA [Veterinary Laboratories Agency]
archive of BSE tissues may apply via the VLA website at <http://www.vla.gov.uk>

--
Steve Edwards
Chief Executive VLA
email <s.edwards@vla.defra.gsi.gov.uk>

[The TSE archive of the VLA can be accessed at
<http://www.defra.gov.uk/corporate/vla/science/science-tse-arc-intro.htm>.
It includes an application form and instructions, as well as the following
comments regarding the review process: "All requests to the Archive are
subject to review by the Independent Archive Advisory Group (IAAG). IAAG
provides an external review to ensure all requests are dealt with fairly.

IAAG consists of 6 researchers from the UK, France and Germany. Officials
from Defra, the Food Standards Agency and the European Commission oversee
the group". - Mod.AS]

